Implement the private `finalize/1` function. It drives contiguous, in-order
finalization of buckets as the watermark advances, and is called after every
push.

`finalize/1` takes the server `state` and returns a (possibly updated) `state`:

- If the grid has not been anchored yet (`next_emit` is `nil`, meaning no point
  has ever been pushed), there is nothing to finalize — return `state`
  unchanged.
- Otherwise, check whether the bucket that is currently awaiting emission (the
  one starting at `next_emit`) is fully closed. A bucket is closed once
  `next_emit + interval + lateness <= watermark`. When it is closed:
  finalize that bucket by piping `state` through `close_bucket/2` (with
  `state.next_emit` as the bucket), then `advance/1`, then recurse into
  `finalize/1` so that any further contiguous buckets are emitted too.
- When the awaiting bucket is not yet closed, stop and return `state`.

Emit buckets one at a time, in ascending order, with no gaps — empty buckets are
finalized the same way (their `:fill` handling lives in `close_bucket/2`). Use
whatever function clauses / recursion you find natural.

